07:51.905 --> 07:53.839
How did you find your way
into Test Pattern?

07:53.841 --> 07:55.207
How did that start?

07:55.209 --> 07:58.777
Well, I was Marky's girlfriend.

07:58.779 --> 08:00.712
We grew up
in New Haven together,

08:00.714 --> 08:03.215
and then when he and Lee
were forming Test Pattern,

08:03.217 --> 08:05.016
they were looking for
a female vocalist,

08:05.018 --> 08:08.520
and I don't know why...

08:08.522 --> 08:11.089
they thought of me,

08:11.091 --> 08:14.626
'cause...
I had never done anything like that,

08:14.628 --> 08:19.064
so I enrolled in CSAD
the following year, and...

08:19.066 --> 08:20.532
and then Lee and I got married.

08:20.534 --> 08:22.801
Wait, Lee?
How did that happen?

08:22.803 --> 08:25.203
Well, it was part of
a performance he was doing

08:25.205 --> 08:27.038
about the banality of marriage,

08:27.040 --> 08:30.075
so he married a lot of objects.

08:30.077 --> 08:32.611
Like a telephone...
you know,

08:32.613 --> 08:35.580
parrot,
and a fancy automobile.

08:35.582 --> 08:37.048
And then I was the only human.

08:53.834 --> 08:55.834
Thank you.

09:00.039 --> 09:03.275
We're seeing the history
of the band sort of unfolding.

09:03.277 --> 09:06.545
and...
we got some more friends.

